applicant has failed to present plans which accurately depict the development
on site. Specifically, the position of the proposed staircase in relation to the existing conservatory is not consistent between the proposed plans and elevations submitted. In addition, the description for a two bedroom flat is not reflected in the plans, as the second bedroom is not detailed. The
proposal could prejudice third parties who may otherwise have wished to comment
on the application; the proposed development cannot be accurately assessed, and
it cannot be demonstrated that it would be supported by the Development Plan.
